# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# This is a CODE-ONLY repository. Simulation trajectories, per-frame
# analysis products, and rendered figures are large and regenerable,
# and are never committed. (The committed data/ CSVs and
# simulation_inputs/ are explicit exceptions, tracked on purpose.)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.venv/
env/

# --- Local data symlinks (machine-specific; create with setup_data_links.sh) ---
# These point at the consolidated trajectory-analysis products on the host and
# are deliberately NOT committed so the repo stays portable. Run
# `bash setup_data_links.sh` (optionally with DATA_ROOT=...) to recreate them.
/PYTHON_ANALYSIS
/PYTHON_SIMULATIONS
/SIMULATION

# --- Analysis run directories & per-frame outputs (regenerated) ---
# NOTE: pipeline outputs land at the repo root or under analysis/ when run there.
# The committed simulation_inputs/lammps_scripts/TEMP_* trees are INPUTS, never matched here.
/TEMP_*/
/analysis/TEMP_*/
ANALYSIS_SG/
ANALYSIS_DSM/
ANALYSIS_NDSM/
ANALYSIS_*_AVE/
CLASSIFY_*/
CORRELATION_CLASSIFY_*/
RESULTS/
SUMMARY/

# --- Rendered figures (final figures live with the manuscript, not here) ---
FIGURES/
FIGURES_SI/
DOMAIN_CONTACT_MAPS/

# --- Large binary trajectory / restart / intermediate artifacts ---
*.lammpstrj
*.dcd
*.xtc
*.trr
*.restart.*
*.npz
*.npy
log.lammps
print.statements
output_*/

# --- Logs ---
logs/
*.log
slurm-*.out
nohup.out

# --- OS / editor cruft ---
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.vscode/
.idea/
